<TITLE> Govt schools start admission form sales Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 13 (bdnews24.com)-A total of 24 government schools in the city start sale of admission forms for Classes 1 to 9 on Sunday, with a view to holding entry exams from the first week of January. "The respective school authorities will sell and receive the forms from 3pm, to 9am," Farid Uddin, assistant director of Secondary and Education Department, told bdnews24.com. "The sales of forms will continue till Dec 27 and Tk 100 will be taken for every form," he said. Students will take tests on the traditional 100 mark system. The schools have been divided in three groupsKa, Kha and Ga that will arrange tests respectively on Jan 4, 6 and 10. Group 'Ka' includes Dhaka Government Laboratory High School, Mirpur Government High School, Matijheel Government Girls' High School, Khilgaon Government High School, Nababpur Government High School, New Government Girls' High School, Islamia Government High School, and Mohammad Government High School. Group 'Kha' includes Matijheel Government Boys' High School, Narinda Government High School, Dhaka Government Muslim High School, Banglabazar Government Girls' High School, Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Boys' High School, Government Bigyan College Adjacent High School, Tejgaon, Dhanmandi Government Girls' High School, Dhanmandi Quamrunnesa Girls' High School. Group 'Ga' includes Armanotola Government High School, Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Government Girls' School, Dhaka Collegiate School, Sadargahat, Gonobhaban Government High School, Tikatuli Quamrunnessa Government Girls' High School, Tejgaon Government Girls' High School and Tejgaon Government High School, and Dhanmandi Government Boys' High School. b
